{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":844,"text":"I used to have this recurring dream"},{"time":2929,"text":"where I'd walk into a roomful of people,"},{"time":6388,"text":"and I'd try not to make\neye contact with anyone."},{"time":10220,"text":"Until someone notices me,"},{"time":11959,"text":"and I just panic."},{"time":14213,"text":"And the person walks up to me,"},{"time":16041,"text":"and says, \"Hi, my name is So-and-so."},{"time":18574,"text":"And what is your name?\""},{"time":20313,"text":"And I'm just quiet, unable to respond."},{"time":25196,"text":"After some awkward silence, he goes,"},{"time":27663,"text":"\"Have you forgotten your name?\""},{"time":29851,"text":"And I'm still quiet."},{"time":32293,"text":"And then, slowly, all the other people\nin the room begin to turn toward me"},{"time":36963,"text":"and ask, almost in unison,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":39830,"text":"(Voice-over, several voices)\n\"Have you forgotten your name?\""},{"time":44616,"text":"As the chant gets louder,\nI want to respond, but I don't."}]},{"cues":[{"time":50350,"text":"I'm a visual artist."},{"time":52754,"text":"Some of my work is humorous,"},{"time":55359,"text":"and some is a bit funny but in a sad way."},{"time":60160,"text":"And one thing that I really enjoy doing"},{"time":64891,"text":"is making these little animations"},{"time":67181,"text":"where I get to do the voice-over\nfor all kinds of characters."},{"time":70979,"text":"I've been a bear."}]},{"cues":[{"time":72261,"text":"(Video) Bear (Safwat Saleem's voice): Hi."}]},{"cues":[{"time":74354,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":76129,"text":"Safwat Saleem: I've been a whale."}]},{"cues":[{"time":77813,"text":"(Video) Whale (SS's voice): Hi."}]},{"cues":[{"time":79526,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":80813,"text":"SS: I've been a greeting card."}]},{"cues":[{"time":82301,"text":"(Video) Greeting card (SS's voice): Hi."}]},{"cues":[{"time":84378,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":85481,"text":"SS: And my personal favorite\nis Frankenstein's monster."}]},{"cues":[{"time":88512,"text":"(Video) Frankenstein's monster\n(SS's voice): (Grunts)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":91233,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":92297,"text":"SS: I just had to grunt\na lot for that one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":94421,"text":"A few years ago,\nI made this educational video"},{"time":97128,"text":"about the history of video games."},{"time":100048,"text":"And for that one, I got to do\nthe voice of Space Invader."}]},{"cues":[{"time":103814,"text":"(Video) Space Invader (SS's voice): Hi."}]},{"cues":[{"time":105894,"text":"SS: A dream come true, really,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":107365,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":108391,"text":"And when that video was posted online,"},{"time":110494,"text":"I just sat there on the computer,\nhitting \"refresh,\""},{"time":113208,"text":"excited to see the response."},{"time":115208,"text":"The first comment comes in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":116646,"text":"(Video) Comment: Great job."},{"time":117964,"text":"SS: Yes!"},{"time":119709,"text":"I hit \"refresh.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":120988,"text":"(Video) Comment: Excellent video.\nI look forward to the next one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":124115,"text":"SS: This was just the first\nof a two-part video."},{"time":126635,"text":"I was going to work\non the second one next."},{"time":128700,"text":"I hit \"refresh.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":129890,"text":"(Video) Comment: Where is part TWO?\nWHEREEEEE? I need it NOWWWWW!: P"}]},{"cues":[{"time":133750,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":135292,"text":"SS: People other than my mom\nwere saying nice things about me,"},{"time":138259,"text":"on the Internet!"},{"time":139449,"text":"It felt like I had finally arrived."},{"time":141806,"text":"I hit \"refresh.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":143132,"text":"(Video) Comment: His voice\nis annoying. No offense."}]},{"cues":[{"time":145855,"text":"SS: OK, no offense taken. Refresh."}]},{"cues":[{"time":148549,"text":"(Video) Comment: Could you remake this\nwithout peanut butter in your mouth?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":152137,"text":"SS: OK, at least the feedback\nis somewhat constructive. Hit \"refresh.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":156628,"text":"(Video) Comment: Please don't use\nthis narrator again"},{"time":159198,"text":"u can barely understand him."}]},{"cues":[{"time":160584,"text":"SS: Refresh."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161759,"text":"(Video) Comment: Couldn't follow\nbecause of the Indian accent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":164763,"text":"SS: OK, OK, OK, two things."},{"time":166271,"text":"Number one, I don't have an Indian accent,"},{"time":168367,"text":"I have a Pakistani accent, OK?"},{"time":170318,"text":"And number two, I clearly\nhave a Pakistani accent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":173482,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":176233,"text":"But comments like that kept coming in,"},{"time":178282,"text":"so I figured I should just ignore them"},{"time":181051,"text":"and start working\non the second part of the video."},{"time":184104,"text":"I recorded my audio,"},{"time":185658,"text":"but every time I sat down to edit,"},{"time":188681,"text":"I just could not do it."},{"time":191688,"text":"Every single time, it would take me\nback to my childhood,"},{"time":194700,"text":"when I had a much harder time speaking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":197934,"text":"I've stuttered for as long\nas I can remember."},{"time":202285,"text":"I was the kid in class"},{"time":203586,"text":"who would never raise his hand\nwhen he had a question --"},{"time":206247,"text":"or knew the answer."},{"time":207445,"text":"Every time the phone rang,"},{"time":208784,"text":"I would run to the bathroom\nso I would not have to answer it."},{"time":212907,"text":"If it was for me, my parents\nwould say I'm not around."},{"time":216140,"text":"I spent a lot of time in the bathroom."},{"time":219721,"text":"And I hated introducing myself,"},{"time":222216,"text":"especially in groups."},{"time":223849,"text":"I'd always stutter on my name,\nand there was usually someone who'd go,"},{"time":227249,"text":"\"Have you forgotten your name?\""},{"time":228800,"text":"And then everybody would laugh."},{"time":230856,"text":"That joke never got old."}]},{"cues":[{"time":234727,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":237635,"text":"I spent my childhood\nfeeling that if I spoke,"},{"time":241466,"text":"it would become obvious\nthat there was something wrong with me,"},{"time":246645,"text":"that I was not normal."},{"time":249070,"text":"So I mostly stayed quiet."},{"time":252142,"text":"And so you see, eventually for me to even\nbe able to use my voice in my work"},{"time":255929,"text":"was a huge step for me."},{"time":257991,"text":"Every time I record audio,"},{"time":259611,"text":"I fumble my way through saying\neach sentence many, many times,"},{"time":263130,"text":"and then I go back in"},{"time":264788,"text":"and pick the ones\nwhere I think I suck the least."}]},{"cues":[{"time":270997,"text":"(Voice-over) SS: Audio editing\nis like Photoshop for your voice."},{"time":274100,"text":"I can slow it down, speed it up,\nmake it deeper, add an echo."},{"time":277935,"text":"And if I stutter along the way,\nand if I stutter along the way,"},{"time":281706,"text":"I just go back in and fix it."},{"time":283349,"text":"It's magic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284768,"text":"SS: Using my highly edited\nvoice in my work"},{"time":287697,"text":"was a way for me\nto finally sound normal to myself."},{"time":292302,"text":"But after the comments on the video,"},{"time":294924,"text":"it no longer made me feel normal."},{"time":297897,"text":"And so I stopped\nusing my voice in my work."},{"time":301984,"text":"Since then, I've thought a lot\nabout what it means to be normal."},{"time":307218,"text":"And I've come to understand"},{"time":309260,"text":"that \"normal\" has a lot to do\nwith expectations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":313307,"text":"Let me give you an example."},{"time":314860,"text":"I came across this story"},{"time":316214,"text":"about the Ancient Greek writer, Homer."},{"time":318504,"text":"Now, Homer mentions\nvery few colors in his writing."},{"time":322650,"text":"And even when he does,"},{"time":324279,"text":"he seems to get them quite a bit wrong."},{"time":326936,"text":"For example, the sea\nis described as wine red,"},{"time":330252,"text":"people's faces are sometimes green\nand sheep are purple."},{"time":334838,"text":"But it's not just Homer."},{"time":336237,"text":"If you look at all\nof the ancient literature --"},{"time":338570,"text":"Ancient Chinese, Icelandic, Greek, Indian"},{"time":340794,"text":"and even the original Hebrew Bible --"},{"time":343495,"text":"they all mention very few colors."},{"time":346745,"text":"And the most popular theory\nfor why that might be the case"},{"time":350149,"text":"is that cultures begin\nto recognize a color"},{"time":352577,"text":"only once they have the ability\nto make that color."},{"time":355686,"text":"So basically, if you can make a color,"},{"time":357560,"text":"only then can you see it."},{"time":359727,"text":"A color like red, which was fairly easy\nfor many cultures to make --"},{"time":363410,"text":"they began to see that color\nfairly early on."},{"time":366265,"text":"But a color like blue,\nwhich was much harder to make --"},{"time":369032,"text":"many cultures didn't begin to learn\nhow to make that color"},{"time":371809,"text":"until much later."},{"time":372999,"text":"They didn't begin to see it\nuntil much later as well."},{"time":375539,"text":"So until then, even though\na color might be all around them,"},{"time":379213,"text":"they simply did not have\nthe ability to see it."},{"time":381682,"text":"It was invisIble."},{"time":382864,"text":"It was not a part of their normal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":386593,"text":"And that story has helped\nput my own experience into context."},{"time":390376,"text":"So when I first read\nthe comments on the video,"},{"time":392870,"text":"my initial reaction was to take it\nall very personally."},{"time":396543,"text":"But the people commenting did not know"},{"time":398465,"text":"how self-conscious I am about my voice."},{"time":402258,"text":"They were mostly reacting to my accent,"},{"time":404929,"text":"that it is not normal\nfor a narrator to have an accent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":409089,"text":"But what is normal, anyway?"},{"time":411473,"text":"We know that reviewers will find\nmore spelling errors in your writing"},{"time":414859,"text":"if they think you're black."},{"time":417144,"text":"We know that professors are less likely\nto help female or minority students."},{"time":422349,"text":"And we know that resumes\nwith white-sounding names"},{"time":425020,"text":"get more callbacks than resumes\nwith black-sounding names."},{"time":429043,"text":"Why is that?"},{"time":431011,"text":"Because of our expectations\nof what is normal."},{"time":434135,"text":"We think it is normal"},{"time":435738,"text":"when a black student has spelling errors."},{"time":438264,"text":"We think it is normal"},{"time":440003,"text":"when a female or minority student\ndoes not succeed."},{"time":443962,"text":"And we think it is normal"},{"time":445625,"text":"that a white employee\nis a better hire than a black employee."},{"time":449399,"text":"But studies also show\nthat discrimination of this kind,"},{"time":452017,"text":"in most cases, is simply favoritism,"},{"time":454086,"text":"and it results more from wanting\nto help people that you can relate to"},{"time":458493,"text":"than the desire to harm people\nthat you can't relate to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":462944,"text":"And not relating to people\nstarts at a very early age."},{"time":466175,"text":"Let me give you an example."},{"time":467949,"text":"One library that keeps track of characters"},{"time":471522,"text":"in the children's book\ncollection every year,"},{"time":474839,"text":"found that in 2014,\nonly about 11 percent of the books"},{"time":480144,"text":"had a character of color."},{"time":482368,"text":"And just the year before,\nthat number was about eight percent,"},{"time":486069,"text":"even though half of American children\ntoday come from a minority background."},{"time":489901,"text":"Half."}]},{"cues":[{"time":491353,"text":"So there are two big issues here."},{"time":493001,"text":"Number one, children are told\nthat they can be anything,"},{"time":495682,"text":"they can do anything,"},{"time":496857,"text":"and yet, most stories\nthat children of color consume"},{"time":499354,"text":"are about people who are not like them."},{"time":501256,"text":"Number two is that majority groups\ndon't get to realize"},{"time":504039,"text":"the great extent to which\nthey are similar to minorities --"},{"time":507096,"text":"our everyday experiences, our hopes,"},{"time":510167,"text":"our dreams, our fears"},{"time":512063,"text":"and our mutual love for hummus."},{"time":513860,"text":"It's delicious!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":515193,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":517911,"text":"Just like the color blue\nfor Ancient Greeks,"},{"time":520618,"text":"minorities are not a part\nof what we consider normal,"},{"time":525440,"text":"because normal is simply a construction\nof what we've been exposed to,"},{"time":530425,"text":"and how visible it is around us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":533590,"text":"And this is where things\nget a bit difficult."},{"time":536714,"text":"I can accept the preexisting notion\nof normal -- that normal is good,"},{"time":541018,"text":"and anything outside of that very\nnarrow definition of normal is bad."},{"time":545758,"text":"Or I can challenge\nthat preexisting notion of normal"},{"time":550462,"text":"with my work"},{"time":552034,"text":"and with my voice"},{"time":554338,"text":"and with my accent"},{"time":556632,"text":"and by standing here onstage,"},{"time":558172,"text":"even though I'm scared shitless\nand would rather be in the bathroom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":561519,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":562860,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":573301,"text":"(Video) Sheep (SS's voice):\nI'm now slowly starting to use my voice"},{"time":576496,"text":"in my work again."},{"time":577674,"text":"And it feels good."},{"time":578849,"text":"It does not mean I won't have a breakdown"},{"time":580841,"text":"the next time a couple dozen\npeople say that I talk"},{"time":583332,"text":"(Mumbling) like I have peanut\nbutter in my mouth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":585664,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":586690,"text":"SS: It just means I now have\na much better understanding"},{"time":589394,"text":"of what's at stake,"},{"time":591162,"text":"and how giving up is not an option."}]},{"cues":[{"time":596519,"text":"The Ancient Greeks didn't just wake up\none day and realize"},{"time":599429,"text":"that the sky was blue."},{"time":601197,"text":"It took centuries, even, for humans\nto realize what we had been ignoring"},{"time":604659,"text":"for so long."},{"time":606893,"text":"And so we must continuously challenge\nour notion of normal,"},{"time":610738,"text":"because doing so is going\nto allow us as a society"},{"time":615094,"text":"to finally see the sky for what it is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":620272,"text":"(Video) Characters: Thank you. Thank you.\nThank you. Thank you. Thank you."},{"time":626060,"text":"Frankenstein's monster: (Grunts)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":627675,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":628710,"text":"SS: Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":629885,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}